1	Chinese Exclusion Act - Wikipedia	The Chinese Exclusion Act was a United States federal law signed by President  Chester A. Arthur on May 6, 1882, prohibiting all immigration of Chinese laborers.  The act followed the Angell Treaty of 1880, a set of revisions to the US–China  Burlingame Treaty of 1868 that allowed the US to suspend Chinese immigration.	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_Exclusion_Act
